            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              Column failure is catastrophic - there's no gradual warning like with beams that sag. When a column 
              fails, the structure above comes down immediately. That's why proper sizing, installation, and lateral 
              support are non-negotiable.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
              The most common mistake we see is using standard adjustable columns for loads exceeding 36 kN. 
              Always calculate actual loads - don't guess. In Toronto basements, moisture is another killer. 
              We've replaced hundreds of rotted wood columns that lacked proper moisture protection.
            </p>
